

This command is used to list all namespaces inside a cluster:
    - kubectl get ns: 

This command is used to list all pods in specific namespaces:
    - kubectl get po -n kube-system

This command is used to list all pods in specific namespaces:
    - kubectl get po -n kube-system

This command is used to create a namespace inside Kubernetes cluster:

    - kubectl create -f namespace-dev.json

            {
                "apiVersion": "v1",
                "kind": "Namespace",
                "metadata": {
                    "name": "development",
                    "labels": {
                        "name": "development"
                    }
                }
            }


This command is used to resolved a specific DNS:
    nslookup google.com

        nslookup: can't resolve '(null)': Name does not resolve

        Name:      google.com
        Address 1: 172.217.30.174 gru14s18-in-f14.1e100.net
        
#################################################################################

This command shows the file that resolve almost all dns inside e Linux enverioment:
    cat /etc/resolv.conf

        nameserver 10.96.0.10 #Resolve DNS cluster
        search default.svc.cluster.local svc.cluster.local cluster.local
        options ndots:5

#################################################################################

This command is used to update an Aphine image:

    - apk update

This command is used to install mysql-client in Aphine Linux:

    - apk apk add mysql-client

This command is used to connect a remote database, in this example we're used a container inside
the cluster:

    - mysql -h database -uroot -ppassword fleetman    

This command is used to get inside a specific Pod:

    - kubectl exec -it POD_NAME sh


